    <note>Chang(2) Gun [3006] XTS, 75B.1b; Renming Da cidian, p. 917. He was ziaxiang under Daizong and Dezong, cashiered at the beginning of Dezong's reign, rehabilitated and ended career as Fujian guancha shi, when he suposedly introduced the people of Min to scholarship with which they had hiterto been unfamiliar and from this time on scholarly pursuits flourished in Min. Reconstruction of this lineage based on the funerary inscriptions of Pu [3009], Gou's [7118] wife, born Li, Tong [7001], Youkai [13505] and Gong(2) [13506] (q.v.). XTS, 75B.1a-1b. QTW, 410.1a. Literary fragments preserved in QTW.</note>
